kpi_info.title: period_duration
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: DATAMISSINGINLA
kpi_info.use: This line is printed if data transfer fromone or several VLRUs failed during one or more inquiries, i.e. only a subset of the data could be collected. It means that the printed LAC values are not reliable. (The problem can be overloaded VLRUs, a VLRU start-up.)

kpi_info.title: TOTALCURRENT
kpi_info.use: Number of normal subscribers in all locationarea at the reporting time. The maximum number of location areas in a report is 40.

kpi_info.title: TOTALAVERAGE
kpi_info.use: Sum of the average numbers of normalsubscribers in all location area. The maximum number of location areas in a report is 40.

kpi_info.title: DATAMISSINGINPAGINGPERLA
kpi_info.use: This line is printed if data transfer fromone or several VLRUs failed during one or more inquiries, that is, only a subset of the data could be collected. It means that the printed counters per LAC are not reliable. (The problem can be overloaded VLRUs, a VLRU start-up.)

kpi_info.title: DATAMISSINGINSUBSCVALUESHLR
kpi_info.use: This line is printed if data transfer fromone or several VLRUs failed during one or more inquiries, that is, only a subset of the data could be collected. It means that the printed subscriber numbers per HLR are not reliable. (The problem can be overloaded VLRUs, a VLRU start-up.)

kpi_info.title: DATAMISSINGINSUBSCVALUESPLMN
kpi_info.use: This line is printed if data transfer fromone or several VLRUs failed during one or more inquiries, that is, only a subset of the data could be collected. It means that the printed subscriber numbers per PLMN are not reliable. (The problem can be overloaded VLRUs, a VLRU start-up.)

kpi_info.title: SIM_CURRENT_REG_TOTAL
kpi_info.use:
Summarized (for all location areas) number of subscribers at the end of the Result Accumulation Period in the VLR with triplet authentication vector. Old counter (M80B2C5 - CURRENT TOTAL) is not available with this counter.
Measured object: VLR

kpi_info.title: SIM_AVG_REG_TOTAL
kpi_info.use:
Summarized average number of subscribers during the Result Accumulation Period in the VLR who have triplet authentication vector.
